==Reception==
{{Over-quotation|date=August 2016}}
"For a romantic comedy, Magikano has precious little romance. Or comedy for that matter. Indeed, with a third of the series already over by the close of this volume, it seems devoid of any ambition at all beyond testing how far sheer hyperactivity can be taken before viewers begin using their DVDs as doggy chew-toys." — Carl Kimlinger, ''[[Anime News Network]]''.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Kimlinger |first=Carl |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/magikano/dvd-1 |title=Magikano DVD 1- A New Witch in Town |work=Anime News Network |date=April 10, 2008 |accessdate=February 13, 2011 }}</ref>
"Magikano has potential based on what's here so I'm curious as to how the two remaining volumes will play out but I'm just expecting more light and silly fun with no real meat to it." — Chris Beveridge, ''Mania''.<ref name="Anime on DVD and Mania"/>
"Magikano has racy girls with magical means with more comedy and twists that harem fans can imaigne!" — Holly Ellingwood, ''activeAnime''.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Ellingwood |first=Holly |url=http://activeanime.com/html/2008/03/04/magikano-vol-2-witch-hunt/ |title=Magikano Vol. 2: Witch Hunt |work=activeAnime |date=March 4, 2008 }}<!-- Formerly at http://www.activeanime.com/html/content/view/2732/57/ --></ref>
"This is a collection of gags in search of a plotline, and when it finally does find a story to tell, the change in tone is so abrupt that you end up wishing it had stayed pointless and stupid." — Carlo Santos, ''Anime News Network''.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Santos |first=Carlo |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/review/magikano/dvd-series-set |title=Magikano DVD Series Set |work=Anime News Network |date=November 11, 2009 |accessdate=February 13, 2011 }}</ref>
