The '''Nintendo Power Line''' was a [[hotline]] that provided readers of ''[[Nintendo Power]]'' magazine hints to their favorite video games on [[Nintendo]] consoles, such as the [[Nintendo Entertainment System]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.retrogamenetwork.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/1.gif|title=Nintendo Power Hotline Advertisement|access-date=2016-11-24}}</ref> It ran from the publishing of the first issue publication of Nintendo Power to June 2010, due to the Internet becoming more widespread.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.retrogamenetwork.com/2013/02/02/so-you-called-the-nintendo-power-line-who-exactly-was-on-the-other-end/|title=So you called the Nintendo Power Line...Who Exactly Was On The Other End?|accessdate=2017-01-27|date=2013-02-02}}</ref> It was revived from November 11 to November 13, 2016 in celebration of the release of the [[NES Classic Edition]].<ref name=CNET>{{cite news|last1=Cooper|first1=Gael|title=Game on! Nintendo's Power Line returns this weekend only|url=https://www.cnet.com/news/nintendo-power-line-returns-nes-classic-edition/|publisher=[[CNET]]|accessdate=2016-11-24|date=2016-11-07}}</ref> The messages, however, were automated rather than being live.<ref name=CNET/>

